In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims September 2018 as National Alcohol and Drug Addiction Recovery Month. He reaffirms his commitment to addressing the stigma of addiction and reminds Americans that recovery is possible. Trump acknowledges that addiction to alcohol and drugs affects millions of Americans and poses a threat to the safety, security, and well-being of the country. He emphasizes the importance of taking action to combat the crisis, including preventing drug abuse, expanding access to treatment and recovery support services, and cutting off the flow of illicit drugs. Trump expresses gratitude to first responders, healthcare providers, and advocates fighting against addiction, and celebrates those in recovery who contribute to efforts to stop drug use. He encourages all Americans struggling with addiction to realize that recovery is possible. Trump calls upon the people of the United States to observe National Alcohol and Drug Addiction Recovery Month with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities.